    <h2>Advantages of the Inverted Triangle Body Type Diet</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Balanced Nutritional Intake: Emphasizing a variety of foods helps maintain a healthy body composition.</li>
        <li>Muscle Maintenance: A protein-rich diet supports lean muscle retention, which is beneficial for metabolism.</li>
        <li>Weight Management: A focus on whole foods aids in weight control and helps minimize fat storage in the upper body.</li>
        <li>Flexibility in Food Choices: The variety of allowed foods prevents dietary monotony and can enhance long-term adherence.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Workout Recommendations for Inverted Triangle Body Type Females</h2>
    <p><strong>Strength Training:</strong> Focus on lower body exercises to create balance and enhance curves, such as:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Squats and lunges for the glutes and thighs</li>
        <li>Deadlifts for overall strength</li>
        <li>Focus on upper body exercises that tone without bulking (e.g., lighter weights with higher reps)</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Cardiovascular Exercise:</strong> Engage in moderate-intensity cardio, such as running, cycling, or swimming, for at least 150 minutes per week to promote heart health and manage weight.</p>
    <p><strong>High-Intensity Interval Training (HIIT):</strong> Incorporate HIIT workouts 1-2 times a week for improved endurance and effective calorie burning.</p>
    <p><strong>Flexibility and Core Work:</strong> Include activities like yoga or Pilates to enhance flexibility, core strength, and posture.</p>

